#: ../../C/cough-and-die.rst:5
msgid "cough and die"
msgstr "cough and die"

#: ../../C/cough-and-die.rst:7
msgid "v\\."
msgstr "動詞"

#: ../../C/cough-and-die.rst:9
msgid ""
"Syn. :ref:`barf`\\. Connotes that the program is throwing its hands up by "
"design rather than because of a bug or oversight. \"The parser saw a "
"control-A in its input where it was looking for a printable, so it coughed "
"and died.\" Compare :ref:`die`\\, :ref:`die-horribly`\\, :ref:`scream-and-"
"die`\\."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`barf`\\ "
"と同義。プログラムがバグや見落としのためではなく、設計によってお手上げになっていることを含意します。「パーサーは印字可能文字を探していた箇所で入力にcontrol-"
"Aを見つけたので、咳き込んで死んだ」。\\ :ref:`die`\\ 、\\ :ref:`die-horribly`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`scream-and-die`\\ と比較せよ。"
